metrics.name: Average FIRST Ready for Review to LAST Closed cycle time
metrics.signalFragment:
AVG(
	(SELECT LAST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN ('Change Status to Closed'))))
	-(SELECT FIRST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN ('Change Status to Ready for Review'))))
   )

metrics.name: Average Creation to To Do cycle time
metrics.description: Average cycle time between two events of interest to the user
metrics.signalFragment:
AVG(
	(SELECT LAST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN (${end_events}))))
	-(SELECT FIRST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN (${start_events}))))
   )

metrics.name: Average cycle time for open cases
metrics.description: Average cycle time for all currently open cases
metrics.signalFragment:
AVG(
	(SELECT LAST(end_time) - FIRST(end_time))) FILTER (
		WHERE (SELECT FIRST(event_name) FILTER (
			WHERE event_name IN (${closing_events}))) IS NULL
   )

metrics.name: Average cycle time
metrics.description: Average cycle time calculated from the first to the last event

metricsVariables.name: closing_events
metricsVariables.description: Events defining the closing of a case, for example 'Clear Invoice', 'Update Opportunity Stage to: Closed Won', 'Reject Quote'

metricsVariables.name: start_events
metricsVariables.description: Events defining the starting point of the process for the cycle time calculation, for example 'Create Sales Order Item'

metricsVariables.name: end_events
metricsVariables.description: Events defining the end point of the process for the cycle time calculation, for example 'Post Goods Issue'

blocks.text: H1: The number of closed tickets goes up towards the end of the engineering quarter
Answer: No. The distribution is roughly even, no peak to be seen at Feb / May / Aug / Nov.
H2: the missing peak is related to larger tickets.
Answer: there is no indication of this, as the ticket duration is not going up. Ticket duration is higher in the beginning of the quarter (assumption: q planning)

dataSource.query: SELECT "Create => Close", "In Progress => Ready for Review" FROM (SELECT (SELECT LAST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to Closed')) - (SELECT FIRST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Create Issue')) as "Create => Close", (SELECT LAST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to Ready for Review')) - (SELECT FIRST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to In Progress')) as "In Progress => Ready for Review" FROM "defaultview-217" WHERE ((SELECT COUNT (EVENT_NAME)) >= 2) AND (SELECT LAST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to Closed')) - (SELECT FIRST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Create Issue')) IS NOT NULL AND (SELECT LAST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to Ready for Review')) - (SELECT FIRST (END_TIME) FILTER (WHERE EVENT_NAME = 'Change Status to In Progress')) IS NOT NULL) as sq TABLESAMPLE EXACT(100 ROWS) REPEATABLE(1676297397885)

children.name: Anomaly in "Average In Progress to Ready for Review cycle time" where "IssueType" is "Bug"
children.description: Metric "Average In Progress to Ready for Review cycle time" is 7.66% lower than mean where "IssueType" is "Bug"

dataSource.query:
SELECT "IssueType", AVG(
	(SELECT LAST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN ('Change Status to Ready for Review'))))
	-(SELECT FIRST(end_time) FILTER (
		WHERE (event_name IN ('Change Status to In Progress'))))
   ) AS "Average In Progress to Ready for Review cycle time" FROM "defaultview-217" WHERE ((SELECT COUNT (EVENT_NAME)) >= 2) GROUP BY 1 LIMIT 500
